◆ fixed_ring_buffer

using wjr::fixed_ring_buffer = basic_ring_buffer<fixed_ring_buffer_storage<T, Alloc>>

A ring_buffer with fixed capacity by construction.

Only allocate memory on construction and deallocation on destruction. After construction, it cannot be expanded and can only be modified through move assignment. For example, ring_buffer that using stack allocator.

◆ ctz() [1/2]

uint32_t wjr::ctz ( const biginteger_data & num)
inlinenoexcept

◆ ctz() [2/2]

template<typename T , WJR_REQUIRES(is_nonbool_unsigned_integral_v< T >) >
WJR_CONST WJR_INTRINSIC_CONSTEXPR20 int wjr::ctz ( T x)
noexcept

Fast count trailing zeros

Very fast even on non-optimized platforms by using a De Bruijn sequence.
Try __builtin_clz if available, otherwise fallback to a portable implementation.
In fallback_clz, use popcount and lowbit if POPCOUNT and POPCNT are available, make sure popcount is fast.
Then use De Bruijn sequence, just a bit slower than popcount + lowbit.

模板参数
TMust be an unsigned integral type

◆ to_chars_unchecked() [3/3]

template<typename Iter , typename Value , unsigned int IBase = 10, typename Converter = char_converter_t, WJR_REQUIRES(charconv_detail::__is_valid_converter_v< Value, Converter >) >
Iter wjr::to_chars_unchecked ( Iter ptr,
Value val,
integral_constant< unsigned int, IBase > ic = {},
Converter conv = {} )
noexcept

Convert an unsigned integer to a string without checking buf size.

Iter can be any output iterator. Support fast_convert mode and fallback mode.
fast_convert mode :
fast_convert mode is used when __is_fast_convert_iterator_v<Iter> is true.
caclulate the number of digits and convert the integer to a string in reverse order.
fallback mode :
use buffer to store the result and use wjr::copy to copy the result to the output iterator.
